               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431127-name-1140" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1140" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1140" type="surname" value="M'GREGOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431127-name-1140" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES M'GREGOR</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 177.) About seven o'clock on Sa<lb></lb>turday evening, the 18th of Nov., I was by the turnpike at the Angel, about a mile and a half from the prosecutor's—I saw the prisoner with this horse<lb></lb>cloth round his shoulders—as soon as he saw me he went to a lamp-post, and wrapped the cloth up—I asked where he brought it from—he said from home, and was going to take it home—I took him, and, about 100 yards from the station, he became very violent, knocked me about, and kicked me—at the station he said he got it from Northumberland-house, in the Green-lanes—I went there, and they did not know it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> In coming from Northumberland-house I picked it up.</p>
